<section class="section-block">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="h3">Start small: a 14-day stewardship plan</h2>

    <div class="grid-2">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Week 1: stabilize inputs</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Morning outdoor light (10–20 min)</li>
          <li>Daily walk or gardening movement (20–40 min)</li>
          <li>One meal/day: whole foods + fiber</li>
          <li>Water + electrolytes as appropriate</li>
          <li>Sleep window: consistent bedtime</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Week 2: add a garden habit</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Plant 2–4 “starter” crops for your zone</li>
          <li>One daily tea/food plant (gentle, low risk)</li>
          <li>Track one metric (sleep, pain, BP, steps)</li>
          <li>Share notes with a clinician if on meds</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="muted" style="margin-top:10px;">
      This guide emphasizes food, movement, and cultivation—then adds herbs cautiously.
      High-dose extracts are not the default.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section-block">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="h3">Safety cautions (quick)</h2>

    <div class="grid-2">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Higher interaction risk</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>St. John’s Wort</strong> (broad medication interactions)</li>
          <li><strong>Kava</strong> (possible liver risk)</li>
          <li><strong>Concentrated extracts</strong> (start low; coordinate)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Safer default forms</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Food use (culinary herbs, spices)</li>
          <li>Gentle teas (low concentration)</li>
          <li>Simple topical infused oils (diluted)</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="muted">Essential oils are concentrated—avoid undiluted skin use.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

